cisive and groundbreaking book, Jennifer Hendricks argues that feminists must overthrow the skewed value system that subordinates women, devalues caregiving, and denies too many the right to parent.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aMothersxLegal status, laws, etczUnited States. 0aMothersxLegal status, laws, etc.zUnited States. 0aParent and child (Law)zUnited States. 0aPregnant womenxLegal status, laws, etczUnited States. 0aPregnant womenxLegal status, laws, etc.zUnited States. 7aLAW / Gender & the Law.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023 Englishz978311131914808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023z9783111318226oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520388277?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520388277423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520388277/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131914-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGCb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023